The paper focuses on transfer learning using unsupervisedly learned relational graphs, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also applies the proposed framework to various tasks in natural language processing (NLP) such as question answering, natural language inference, and sentiment analysis, which suggests that it could also be categorized under computational linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper applies the framework to image classification, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The use of deep learning techniques and neural networks in the proposed framework also suggests that it could be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the generic nature of the learned graphs and their potential for transfer to different embeddings, which could be categorized under social and information networks (cs.SI).
